###  http://www.semanticweb.org/nesy4vrd/ontologies/vrd_world#VRDWorldThing
vrd:VRDWorldThing rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:comment """The domain modelled by this ontology is the domain of object classes and predicates recognised in (a customised version of) the annotations of the images of the VRD dataset. This domain equates (roughly, and sparsely) to the material world.  We refer to this domain as the 'VRD material world', that is, the material world as represented by the object classes and predicates of the image annotations of the VRD dataset.

We think of the VRD material world as consisting of a finite number of types (classes) of 'thing'. Class VRDMaterialWorldThing is the top-level (most general) concept (thing) in the model of the VRD material world domain."""@en ;
                  rdfs:label "VRD domain thing"@en .


