###  http://www.semanticweb.org/nesy4vrd/ontologies/vrd_world#has
vrd:has rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
        rdfs:comment """Property 'has' is one of the most common and most general purpose predicates in the visual relationship annotations of the VRD dataset. In the original VRD training set annotations it's used with 66 distinct 'subject' object classes and 81 distinct 'object' object classes.

It has diverse meanings/usages:
a) 'has' as a sort of inverse of a notional 'part of' relation, eg (tower, has, clock)
b) 'has' as in 'wear', eg (person, has, shirt)
c) 'has' as in hosts or supports, eg (table, has, plate)
d) 'has' as in 'hold' or 'with' or 'carry', eg (person, has, bag)

Predicate 'has' is used with so many VRD images we simply have to accept this diversity of meaning. A key consequence of this diversity, however, is that it's not feasible to restrict the domain/range of this property in any meaningful way, or to declare other defining characteristics (such as equivalence, inverses, symmetry, etc.).  There is, in effect, virtually nothing we can say about this general purpose property to describe or constrain its use."""@en .


