###  http://www.semanticweb.org/nesy4vrd/ontologies/vrd_world#in
vrd:in rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
       rdfs:comment """Property 'in' has three very different primary meanings/usages:

1) spatial relation, as in 'inside': eg (dog, in, basket)

2) verb, as in 'wear': eg (person, in, shirt)

3) 'surrounded by' or 'amongst' or 'in the midst of': eg (giraffe, in, grass) or (person, in, street)

Due to its usage as a spatial relation, its domain and range cannot be restricted because, in general, anything can be  located 'on' anything else. And due to the multiple diverse meanings, it's not feasible to describe other defining characteristics either."""@en .


