###  http://www.semanticweb.org/nesy4vrd/ontologies/vrd_world#MixedEnvironmentThing
vrd:MixedEnvironmentThing rdf:type owl:Class ;
                          rdfs:subClassOf vrd:VRDWorldThing ;
                          rdfs:comment """This category of VRDMaterialWorldThing refers to either 1) things that don't sit comfortably within one of the other 3 categories (Natural, Engineered or Cultural things), or 2) classes used in property domain/range restrictions that contain mixtures of things that span the othe 3 categories (Natural, Engineered or Cultural) of things.

This category was originally conceived as a home for a single class, Street, whose members (example objects in VRD images) spanned the natural and human-made environments. It soon, however, became a natural home for many other classes defined from the union of other arbitrary classes spanning the natural and human-made environments."""@en .


