                                                            owl:versionIRI <http://www.semanticweb.org/nesy4vrd/ontologies/vrd_world/1.0> ;
                                                            dc:description """This ontology, VRD-World,  is a well-aligned companion to the NeSy4VRD dataset.

The NeSy4VRD dataset consists of the images of the VRD dataset and their associated NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations. The NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations are a highly customised and quality-improved version of the original VRD visual relationship annotations. 

This ontology, VRD-World, describes the domain of the NeSy4VRD dataset as reflected in the NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations.  An annotated visual relationship is a 5-tuple, (subj_bbox, subj_class, predicate, obj_bbox, obj_class), where subj_bbox and subj_class are the bounding box and class of a 'subject' object, and obj_bbox and obj_class are the bounding box and class of an 'object' object. The predicate describes some relation between this ordered pair of objects. So an annotated visual relationship can, for simplicity, be thought of as being a 3-tuple: (subject, predicate, object).  Each instance of an annotated visual relationship is associated with one unique VRD image and describes a particular relation between a particular ordered pair of objects within that image. A bounding box is specified using 4 integers representing two opposing corners of the box: xmin, ymin, xmax, ymax. An example visual relationship for a particular image, described in 3-tuple form, is: (person, ride, horse).

The VRD-World ontology is designed to capture all of the information contained in the NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations. This includes representations of 1) the VRD images themselves, 2) all of the objects annotated for each image (including their assigned classes and their bounding boxes with their particular bounding box specifications), and 3) all of the predicates describing relations between particular objects.  Each object class referenced within the NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations has a corresponding class within the VRD-World class hierarchy; each predicate referenced within the NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations has a corresponding VRD-World object property.

One can load the NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations in their entirety  into a knowledge graph governed by the VRD-World ontology, extract them again, and reconstitute the NeSy4VRD visual relationship annotations completely, in their native format, without loss of information."""@en ;
